Name: Keshan disease
Definition: A nutritional deficiency that is disease characterized by a cardiomyopathy secondary to selenium deficiency.

Name: obsolete rhinotracheitis
Definition: An upper respiratory tract disease involving inflammation of the nasal cavities and trachea caused by feline herpesvirus 1

Name: obsolete entomophthoromycosis
Definition: A subcutaneous mycosis that involves fungal infection of the subcutaneous tissue caused by members of the order Entomophthorales.

Name: obsolete cutaneous mucormycosis
Definition: An opportunistic mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in cutaneous tissues or located_in subcutaneous tissues followed by a traumatic implantation of fungal elements through the skin

Name: obsolete gastrointestinal mucormycosis
Definition: A opportunistic mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in gastrointestinal tract

Name: obsolete pulmonary mucormycosis
Definition: An opportunistic mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in lungs

Name: obsolete rhinocerebral mucormycosis
Definition: An opportunistic mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in nose

Name: obsolete disseminated paracoccidioidomycosis
Definition: A primary systemic mycosis that results_in systemic fungal infection through hematogenous spread

Name: obsolete pulmonary paracoccidioidomycosis
Definition: A primary systemic mycosis that results_in inflammation located_in lungs

Name: obsolete disseminated sporotrichosis
Definition: A primary systemic mycosis that results_in systemic fungal infection through hematogenous spread

Name: obsolete lymphocutaneous sporotrichosis
Definition: A primary systemic mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in skin and located_in subcutaneous tissue

Name: obsolete pulmonary sporotrichosis
Definition: A primary systemic mycosis that results_in fungal infection located_in lung

Name: biotin deficiency
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by thinning of the hair (often with loss of hair color)

Name: thiamine deficiency disease
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by low levels of thiamine.

Name: vitamin K deficiency bleeding
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by easy bleeding due to an inability to form blood clots caused by vitamin K deficiency

Name: acquired night blindness
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by vitamin A deficiency causing poor adaptation of the eyes to low levels of light
Synonym: vitamin A deficiency with night blindness (disorder)

Name: iron deficiency anemia
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by pallor
Synonym: calculus of bile duct with acute cholecystitis

Name: protein-energy malnutrition
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by inadequate dietary protein and calories
Synonym: partial loss or necrosis of ear ossicles

Name: obsolete protein deficiency
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by inadequate dietary protein and calories

Name: obsolete macrodactylia of fingers
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by inadequate dietary protein and calories

Name: endemic goiter
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease characterized by noncancerous enlargement of the thyroid gland and has_material_basis_in iodine deficiency.

Name: pernicious anemia
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by a decrease in red blood cells due to malabsorption of vitamin B12

Name: scurvy
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by vitamin C (ascorbic acid) deficiency and has_symptom fatigue

Name: folic acid deficiency anemia
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by a decrease in red blood cells due to lack of folate

Name: copper deficiency myelopathy
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by deficiency of copper

Name: ariboflavinosis
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by stomatitis

Name: pyridoxine deficiency anemia
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by normocytic anemia associated with deficiency of pyridoxine (vitamin B6)

Name: choline deficiency disease
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by deficiency of choline

Name: pellagra
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by deficiency of niacin (vitamin B3)

Name: obsolete Thiamine and niacin deficiency state
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by deficiency of niacin (vitamin B3)

Name: obsolete vitamin B 12 deficiency
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by deficiency of niacin (vitamin B3)

Name: obsolete arthropathy associated with hematological disorder
Definition: A nutritional deficiency disease that is characterized by deficiency of niacin (vitamin B3)
